Nicholas Tooth, 25, was playing for the Quirindi Lions against the Narrabri Blue Boars in mid-north NSW on Saturday  . 
  He hit his head on an opponent's shoulder during a tackle and collapsed . 
  Mr Tooth was airlifted to Newcastle's John Hunter Hospital but died late on Sunday . 
  He was visiting his hometown in the New England region of NSW . 
  Tributes have poured in for the young man who was a 'great bloke'